The paper deals with the optimization of scheduling distributed energy resources using metaheuristic algorithms, which falls under the category of optimization and control. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of microservices, container virtualization, and publish/subscribe messaging paradigm, which are related to distributed computing and system architecture, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) the second likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the uncertain nature of renewable energy resources and balancing load and generation, which are related to control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) the third likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of intelligent distributed energy resource plants, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of scheduling, which involves programming languages and compilers, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) the fifth likely sub-category.
